##False negatives cause concern, inflection points are too early to tell, and 33 other news stories

Micro signal

What happened before the Earth was destroyed?

According to Dr. Syzygium aromaticum's real time data, as of Feb. 8,2020, there were 34,662 confirmed cases, 27,657 suspected cases, 3,465 new confirmed cases, and 4,214 new suspected cases in China. There were 6101 severe cases, 724 deaths and 2314 cured cases.

Development of epidemic situation

1. THROAT SWAB NUCLEIC ACID test in patients with "Sanyin" infection. On the afternoon of February 7, a story spread on the Internet, according to the HSINKING newspaper. According to the source, a febrile pneumonia patient from Wuhan to Beijing who was diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia in four Chinese and Japanese hospitals on February 5 was waiting to be transferred to a designated hospital. The patient was admitted to the hospital on January 30 as a severe case of H1N1 because of negative nucleic acid test and positive H1N1 nucleic acid test in her throat swabs. After admission, he was intubated and aspirated. He was found positive for the new coronavirus by bronchoalveolar lavage.

Beijing, a Trijia hospital respiratory doctor told reporters, routine for suspected patients twice throat swab nucleic acid testing, if there is a positive diagnosis, if there are two negative, the basic rule out infection. All three throat swabs tested negative for novel coronavirus nucleic acid, indicating that the virus is highly latent.

2. The diamond princess has 64 confirmed cases so far. The Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare confirmed on February 8 that three people on board the diamond princess had been infected with COVID-19. To date, including the cruise ship has been confirmed 64 cruise ship infection.

3. World Dream Cruise confirmed 8 people. Infected may exceed expectations. According to the HSINKING newspaper, eight people were confirmed on the World Dream cruise from Guangzhou on January 19,108 of the approximately 4,000 passengers were from Hubei Province. They arrived at Nha Trang and Da Nang in Vietnam on January 21 and 22, and returned to Guangzhou on January 24. But it was not until February 1st that a passenger was diagnosed with NCP. During this period, the "world dream" made two more voyages from Hong Kong to the Philippine Port of Manila and Kaohsiung in Taiwan on January 26 and February 2 respectively. It was refused permission to stop in Kaohsiung on February 4. Currently, 3,600 people on board are being quarantined.

Future Studies

1. It's too early to call it a turning point in Zhong Nanshan. "The number of new cases has not continued to increase significantly... but does this mean an inflection point is coming? It's too early to say, " Zhong Nanshan said in a response to CCTV's "common concern" on Feb. 7. It remains to be seen how effective drug research and development will be, "The main treatment for severe or critically ill patients is life support, " he said. "for Chinese medicine, we don't expect it to have a strong anti-viral effect, but it can help improve symptoms in patients with mild illness. "

Mikell Rui'an, director of the World Health Organization Health Emergency Program, also said it was too early to predict when the outbreak would peak.

2. Aerosol transmission of new coronavirus is yet to be clear, experts suggest "Ningxinqiju. ". At a briefing on the prevention and control of COVID-19 in Shanghai on February 8, health and epidemic prevention experts said direct, aerosol and contact transmission were the main routes of COVID-19 infection. Aerosol transmission refers to the mixing of droplets in the air, the formation of aerosols, inhalation leads to infection. Ningbo has previously disclosed a case of the infected and confirmed patients to stay close to the 15-second infection, is thought to be linked to the high concentration of viruses in the vegetable farms, the spread of aerosols. Sciencenet says more evidence is needed. Cao Junji, a researcher at the Institute of Earth Environment and Director of the Aerosol Chemistry and Physics Laboratory of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, told Sciencenet that the current epidemic prevention strategy should "rather believe that it exists" so as not to lose the golden opportunity.

Urban Prevention and control

1. There is a continuing global shortage of protective equipment. The world is facing a chronic shortage of face masks and gloves due to the COVID-19 pneumonia outbreak, and demand is now 100 times the normal level, the personal protective equipment said Feb. 7, according to the UN website, prices are more than 20 times normal. The director general of the WHO, personal protective equipment, said on social media on twitter that the shortage had been exacerbated by improper use and that orders had been outstanding for four to six months, global stocks of masks and inhalers are no longer sufficient to meet the needs of WHO and its partners.

2. Beijing, China: The U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and the World Health Organization refuse to help. More than a month ago, the CDC proposed to Beijing that it send a team of experts to monitor the development of the COVID-19 and provide necessary assistance, according to the New York Times. The World Health Organization made the same recommendation two weeks ago. However, Beijing has yet to respond to the proposals. Diplomats interviewed by The New York Times said this may be because Beijing does not want the world to realize that it needs outside help to deal with the COVID-19 epidemic.

3. Foshan, Hubei Province, can be diagnosed without waiting for nucleic acid detection. On the evening of February 7, the People's Daily micro-blog said that "CT as a rapid diagnosis has unique advantages, in Hubei and other areas with severe epidemic, CT screening may become the first choice for diagnosis. ". Previously, Zhang Xiaochun and other doctors have called for the use of CT imaging to confirm diagnosis, because nucleic acid testing usually takes 3-5 days to produce results, and repeated testing, unable to timely diagnosis and treatment. Only the nucleic acid test was positive for "new coronary pneumonia" .

4. Foshan, Wuhan -- materials are still in short supply. On the evening of February 7, the Deputy Mayor of Wuhan, Hu Yabo, said at a "regular press conference on the prevention and control of the COVID-19 pneumonia in Hubei Province" that there was still a shortage of medical supplies in Wuhan, for example, on February 6, medical protective clothing in Wuhan was 59,900 pieces, with a gap of 41,400 pieces, N95 mask was 119,000 pieces, with a gap of 56,800 pieces The daily requirement for medical goggles, including face masks, was 22,500, with a shortfall of 19,200. Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital and Hankou Hospital are recruiting 15 doctors in internal medicine and critical care medicine respectively.

5. Foshan Raytheon Mountain Hospital, Wuhan, China. Wuhan Raytheon Mountain Hospital preparations are under way in an orderly manner, the first batch of medical team members have been stationed, February 8 will receive and treat the first batch of patients. The hospital will open 32 wards and 1,500 beds to treat patients with confirmed COVID-19 pneumonia.

Beginning on the morning of February 6, the Guanggu district renovation project of Huazhong University of Science and Technology began. When completed, the COVID-19 will be used to isolate and treat patients with severe pneumonia. This used to be an oncology ward, and after three days of renovation, it will have 800 beds.

9. Foshan district, Chengdu, limits the entry of outsiders. Since February 7th Chengdu has been closed to outsiders. The scope includes urban residential areas (courtyards) , farmers concentrated residential areas, rural scattered courtyard. Chengdu residents get a green card to live in and out.

10. Total closed management of Residential Quarter in Foshan, Lanzhou. According to Lanzhou Municipal Party Committee Publicity Department Wechat Public Number News, the city's residential areas to implement closed management. In accordance with the requirements of the grid management, the residential quarters under property management shall be supervised by the local streets to fulfill the responsibilities of the main body of the epidemic prevention and Control Company in the Residential Quarters under property management; the non-residential quarters shall, in accordance with the territorial principle, by the community cadres, community police, grid members, volunteers to form a special team to implement closed management and other prevention and control measures. All the community to close unnecessary access, access personnel must wear masks, do not wear masks in and out of the staff to advise back. Those who forcibly "break the post or punch the card" shall be severely dealt with by the Public Security Bureau in accordance with the law.

Kill. Medical Respirator in Florida, Heilongjiang. Heilongjiang's response to the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic command issued notice No. 8 on February 7, to advocate the use of medical masks or N95KN95 and above standard particulate protection masks by the people in Heilongjiang Province according to their personal wishes, according to the 1:5 ratio, one medical protective mask was replaced, five disposable medical masks were replaced, and one disposable medical mask was replaced. Replacement activities should be strictly in accordance with the standards of good quality clearance, to ensure replacement mask brand new unused.

12. A total of 101 passengers with abnormal body temperature have been found at Hongqiao hub in Shanghai. On February 8, Shanghai held a press conference to introduce the prevention and control of pneumonia in the COVID-19. Hongqiao's airport and Shanghai Hongqiao Railway Station now have 16 checkpoints, 50 medical staff, 100 police and 260 volunteers. All arriving passengers at Hongqiao terminal are subject to at least two customs checks: infrared temperature measurement, public health cloud platform registration of health information and volunteer guidance to fill in. As of February 7, there were 1.22 million temperature readings at the Hongqiao Hub, of which 101 were found to have abnormal body temperatures and 120 were transferred to 60 hospitals.

3. The State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine recommends Qingfei detoxification soup. On February 7, the National Health Commission and the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine jointly issued a notice recommending the use of "Qingfei Paidu decoction" based on recent clinical treatment and observation of therapeutic effects of traditional Chinese and Western medicine. The formula contains asarum, which was previously suspected to be aristolochic acids, and is irreversible and permanently carcinogenic. Ye Zuguang, a researcher at the Chinese Academy of Traditional Chinese Medicine, said in 2018 that, "In 2005, the newly revised National Pharmacopoeia banned the three drugs, Radix Aristolochiae, radix aucklandiae and Aristolochia Manshuriensis, which are considered to contain high aristolochic acids. At the same time, the most heavily used species of Aristolochiaceae, asarum, was restricted to the underground, where tests found almost no aristolochic acids.".

4. State Post Bureau calls for fast food delivery men to be allowed in. At present, many communities in the country are semi-closed management, resulting in courier and delivery can not enter the community. In response, Hou Yanbo, Deputy Director General of the State Post Bureau, said at a State Council news conference that the risk of transmission of the new coronavirus through courier mail is extremely low. He also urges that neighborhoods with smart boxes open the door for couriers, and that neighborhoods without smart boxes be set aside for mail and delivery.

5. A special section of the Tokyo Olympic Organizing Committee, as a response to the outbreak, in Tokyo, Japan. Tokyo Olympic Organizing Committee affairs chief Takeshi Toshiro as new department head. According to NHK, Takefuji said: "We need to calm down, and of course we can not do without a sense of crisis. The Olympics will be held without problems, but in order to hold a safe and secure Congress, we need to adopt an effective response strategy. "
